Camille Stewart Gloster has been appointed as Deputy National Cyber Director for Technology and Ecosystem Security by the Office of the National Cyber Director (ONCD). In this role, she will lead efforts to strengthen the security and development of the US cyber ecosystem. Stewart Gloster is highly regarded in the field of cybersecurity, having worked in both the private and public sectors, including serving in the Obama-Biden Administration at the U.S. Department of Homeland Security. She is known for her advocacy for diversity in the cyber field and is the co-founder of #ShareTheMicInCyber.